Our team has grown over
the past several years.

00:01:18.040 --> 00:01:19.800
And so it used to
be the case we were

00:01:19.800 --> 00:01:21.559
working with some developers.

00:01:21.559 --> 00:01:23.600
Now, we're working with
more and more developers.

00:01:23.600 --> 00:01:26.016
We want to be working with as
many developers as possible.

00:01:26.016 --> 00:01:27.240
And so we'll talk about that.

00:01:27.240 --> 00:01:28.781
In terms of the
products, we'll focus

00:01:28.781 --> 00:01:30.000
on store listing experiments.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:32.280
It has been out since
Google I/O last year,

00:01:32.280 --> 00:01:34.110
but has been very successful.

00:01:34.110 --> 00:01:37.520
Pre-registration is another
thing that we'll talk about.

00:01:37.520 --> 00:01:39.036
Play games services is another.

00:01:39.036 --> 00:01:40.660
And then finally,
talking a bit further

00:01:40.660 --> 00:01:45.600
on in the future in terms of new
technologies and new platforms.

00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:48.839
So first on benchmarking
and working with all of you.

00:01:48.839 --> 00:01:51.130
So retention benchmarking is
something to keep in mind.

00:01:51.130 --> 00:01:54.400
And so this is public data
that was launched last year

00:01:54.400 --> 00:01:57.960
in terms of what the retention
curves for top games look like.

00:01:57.960 --> 00:02:01.420
And I bring this up just
because as mobile games,

00:02:01.420 --> 00:02:03.549
as the market
evolves and matures,

00:02:03.549 --> 00:02:06.090
many times when you're trying
to get a player into your game,

00:02:06.090 --> 00:02:08.119
you're competing with
what that person is

00:02:08.119 --> 00:02:10.410
doing right now, which is
probably playing other games.

00:02:10.410 --> 00:02:11.909
And so it's really
important to keep

00:02:11.909 --> 00:02:13.950
in mind what your
metrics need to look

00:02:13.950 --> 00:02:16.230
like to make a
successful long-term game

00:02:16.230 --> 00:02:19.180
and having that discipline
even before you're launching.

00:02:19.180 --> 00:02:21.940
And so we're increasingly
working with developers

00:02:21.940 --> 00:02:24.410
to help them have these best
practices, understanding what

00:02:24.410 --> 00:02:27.310
is the state of the art and what
are the best developers doing

00:02:27.310 --> 00:02:29.640
today.

00:02:29.640 --> 00:02:31.690
Also, I would
encourage-- so many

00:02:31.690 --> 00:02:33.150
of you we're already
working with.

00:02:33.150 --> 00:02:37.180
For any developers that are in
the audience today that are not

00:02:37.180 --> 00:02:39.500
yet working with the
Play Games BD team,

00:02:39.500 --> 00:02:42.010
I would definitely encourage
you to check out this link,

00:02:42.010 --> 00:02:46.110
g.co/play/gamesBD.

00:02:46.110 --> 00:02:47.880
So it's a quick form.

00:02:47.880 --> 00:02:49.540
We review every
single submission

00:02:49.540 --> 00:02:50.820
we get into this form.

00:02:50.820 --> 00:02:54.784
And we're trying to manage
more and more developers.

00:02:54.784 --> 00:02:56.200
But we will ask
you for some data.

