having thinner drivers,

00:18:10.580 --> 00:18:13.550
just having more
maintainability on your side.

00:18:13.550 --> 00:18:17.360
So not relying on driver vendors
to update their software,

00:18:17.360 --> 00:18:21.122
but giving more control to the
game developers themselves,

00:18:21.122 --> 00:18:23.080
so that you don't need
to deal with differences

00:18:23.080 --> 00:18:24.990
across the hardware ecosystem.

00:18:24.990 --> 00:18:27.710
So there's a lot
of value to Vulkan.

00:18:27.710 --> 00:18:29.580
And we're supporting
that in Android

00:18:29.580 --> 00:18:30.770
in a standards-based way.

00:18:30.770 --> 00:18:34.030
And so we're very
excited about its future.

